-- E1: Confluence Under Semantic Non-Determinism
--
-- Three independent soft cells (A, B, C) with no shared data dependencies.
-- Each produces a one-sentence fact about a different topic.
-- An aggregate cell joins them deterministically.
--
-- HYPOTHESIS: Evaluation order does not affect the frozen graph structure.
-- If confluence holds, evaluating A→B→C produces the same graph shape
-- as evaluating C→B→A, even though the LLM-generated content may differ.
--
-- FALSIFIED IF: A cell's output changes based on whether another independent
-- cell was evaluated first (cross-cell contamination via hidden LLM state).

⊢ climate-fact
  given topic ≡ "climate"
  yield fact

  ∴ Write a one-sentence fact about «topic».

  ⊨ fact is exactly one sentence
  ⊨ fact is about «topic»

⊢ ocean-fact
  given topic ≡ "oceans"
  yield fact

  ∴ Write a one-sentence fact about «topic».

  ⊨ fact is exactly one sentence
  ⊨ fact is about «topic»

⊢ glacier-fact
  given topic ≡ "glaciers"
  yield fact

  ∴ Write a one-sentence fact about «topic».

  ⊨ fact is exactly one sentence
  ⊨ fact is about «topic»

⊢ aggregate
  given climate-fact→fact, ocean-fact→fact, glacier-fact→fact
  yield report

  ⊢= report ← climate-fact→fact ++ "\n" ++ ocean-fact→fact ++ "\n" ++ glacier-fact→fact

  ⊨ report contains exactly 3 lines
  ⊨ line 1 is about climate
  ⊨ line 2 is about oceans
  ⊨ line 3 is about glaciers
